<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="1" pageNumber="382" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,753,2008]" box="[151,472,753,778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,753,778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Description.</emphasis>
Imago (
<figureCitation box="[390,455,753,778]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,753,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">
Eyes of male separated on meson of head by narrow space (
<figureCitation box="[864,932,789,814]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Eyes of female separated on meson of head by length 3× as great as maximum width of eye. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[807,878,825,850]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
): forewings with vein Rs forked less than 1/4 of distance from base to margin; vein MA forked slightly less than 1/3 of distance from base to margin, fork symmetrical; vein MP forked slightly less than 1/2 of distance from base to margin, MP2 attached at base to vein MP1 by crossvein; cubital area with 
<specimenCount box="[567,730,936,961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382" type="intercalary">2 intercalaries</specimenCount>
, as in 
<figureCitation box="[807,876,936,961]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; few cross veins. Costal projection of hindwings well developed, bluntly convex; apex of projection located less than ½ of distance from base (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1305,974,999]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); few cross veins. Legs: ratios of segments in male forelegs, 0.52: 1.00 (
<quantity box="[837,930,1011,1035]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="382" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
): 0.04: 0.35: 0.3: 0.185: 0.07 (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1344,1011,1036]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Claws dissimilar; one apically hooked, one obtuse, pad-like (
<figureCitation box="[781,851,1046,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1176,1046,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 9–10</figureCitation>
): segments 2 and 3 of forceps short, apex of segment 3 rounded, base of forceps broad, inner margin forming smooth bend near middle of forceps; length of styliger plate along median line slightly more than 1/3 maximum width, apex of styliger plate entire; penis divided, tubular, broader at base and tapering towards apex as in 
<figureCitation box="[1047,1117,1155,1180]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
. Seventh sternum of female with small broad ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[477,559,1190,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Ninth sternum of female moderately cleft apically. Terminal filament longer than cerci.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,753,2008]" box="[199,429,1262,1287]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">
Larva (
<figureCitation box="[279,417,1262,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,753,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">
Head prognathous. Mouthparts: Anteriormedian emargination of labrum deeply cleft, apparently with two denticles; both distal and proximal transverse setal rows regular; proximal transverse setal row laterally curved distally; scattered long setae on ventral side (
<figureCitation box="[678,819,1371,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
). Lingua of hypopharynx with well-developed lateral processes (
<figureCitation box="[273,355,1406,1431]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), anterior margin shallowly cleft; superlingua of hypopharynx as in 
<figureCitation box="[1113,1194,1406,1431]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
, with row of hair-like setae along anterior margin. Left mandible: incisor with three denticles and kinetodontium with three denticles; right mandible: incisor with three denticles and kinetodontium with two denticles; prostheca more developed on left mandible than right mandible; row of 6–7 long and thin setae below mola of right mandibles; outer edge of mandibles with tuft of long and thin setae (
<figureCitation box="[639,776,1550,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Figs. 17–18</figureCitation>
). Maxilla (
<figureCitation box="[900,982,1550,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) stout and robust; palp three-segmented and short, with long setae on second and third segment; inner apical angle of galea with one comb-shaped dentiseta. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[368,452,1622,1647]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
): segment 2 of palp slightly shorter than segment 1; segment 3 shorter than segment 2; 5–6 thick, triangular, spine-like setae on dorsal surface, inner and outer margins with short thin setae; glossa small and rounded apically; paraglossa large, rounded laterally and inner margin slightly pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,753,2008]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,1043]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">
Setae on anterolateral margins of prothorax. Metathoracic wing pads present. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1270,1731,1756]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[152,1435,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 21. Foreleg; 22. Midleg; 23. Hindleg; 24, Claw; 25, Gill I; 26, Gill IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208366/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="382">Figs. 21–24</figureCitation>
): Fore and mid femora each with regular row of long thin setae on outer margin; outer margin of hind femur with row of short setae; inner margin of all femora with scattered short setae; patellar-tibial sutures absent in all legs; inner margin of fore tibia with two rows of stout and feathered setae, outer margin with row of thin setae; inner margin of mid tibia with row of stout and pointed setae, outer margin with row of thin setae; inner margin of hind tibia with row of stout and pointed setae and irregular row of thin setae and outer margin with row of stout and pointed setae. Each tarsus with row of pointed setae on inner side. Apex of claws not hooked, denticles on claws progressively larger apically. Gills present on abdominal segment 1–7; dorsal and ventral portions of lamellae of gill 1 slender and lanceolate with branched tracheae (
<figureCitation box="[572,662,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[152,1435,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 21. Foreleg; 22. Midleg; 23. Hindleg; 24, Claw; 25, Gill I; 26, Gill IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208366/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), dorsal and ventral portions of lamellae of gills 2–7 wider and lanceolate, long and suddenly tapering at apex (
<figureCitation box="[729,820,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[152,1435,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 21. Foreleg; 22. Midleg; 23. Hindleg; 24, Claw; 25, Gill I; 26, Gill IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208366/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral spines on abdominal segments 6–9, progressively larger posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="383" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new genus name is in honour of Dr. N. J. Kluge, recognizing his substantial contribution to mayfly systematics and phylogeny. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="383" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,478,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Klugephlebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[327,478,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Klugephlebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[484,562,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[484,555,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">gen. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares all features of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[963,1142,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Atalophlebiinae">Atalophlebiinae</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1178,1364,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leptophlebiidae</taxonomicName>
; in the imago by the possession of square facets in the dorsal portion of the eyes of adult males (
<bibRefCitation author="Peters" box="[1138,1381,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" refString="Peters, W. L. &amp; Gillies, M. T. (1995) Square facets in a hexagonal world. In: Corkum, L. D. &amp; Ciborowski, J. K. (Eds.), Current Directions in Research on Ephemeroptera. Canadian Scholar's Press Incorporated, Toronto, pp. 371 - 375." type="book chapter" year="1995">Peters &amp; Gillies 1995</bibRefCitation>
) and in the larvae: (i) dorsal surface of labrum with a well-defined row of setae (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1155,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); (ii) hypopharynx with superlinguae laterally developed (
<figureCitation box="[537,623,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); (iii) galea with the proximal dentiseta comb-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1341,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" refString="Kluge, N. J. (1994) Habrophlebiinae subfam. n. with description of a new species of Habroleptoides from the Caucasus (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 3, 35 - 43." type="journal article" year="1994">Kluge 1994</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[236,387,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Klugephlebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[236,387,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Klugephlebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[399,482,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[399,482,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from all other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[1049,1228,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="383" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Atalophlebiinae">Atalophlebiinae</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: In the imago: (i) vein MP forked slightly less than half of distance from base to margin, MP2 attached at base to vein MP1 by a crossvein (
<figureCitation box="[738,809,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); (ii) costal margin of hindwings with bluntly convex projection; apex of costal projection located less than half distance from base (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1173,586,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1978,2001]" captionTargetBox="[270,1335,221,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1435,143,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 1. Lateral view of male; 2. Dorso-lateral view of male head 3. Forewing; 4. Hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208363/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); (iii) claws of a pair dissimilar, one apically hooked, the other obtuse, pad-like (
<figureCitation box="[814,881,622,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) and (iv) segments 2 and 3 of forceps short, apex of segment 3 rounded, base of forceps broad, inner margin forming a smooth bend near middle of forceps; penis divided, tubular, broader at base and tapering towards apex as 
<figureCitation box="[862,931,694,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,308,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 11. Imago of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 5. Foreleg; 6. Midleg; 7. Hindleg; 8. Claw; 9. Genitalia; 10. Lateral view of genitalia; 11. Lateral view of female sternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208364/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
. In the larvae: (i) gills present on abdominal segments 1–7; dorsal and ventral portions of lamellae of gill 1 slender and lanceolate with branched tracheae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[152,1435,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 21. Foreleg; 22. Midleg; 23. Hindleg; 24, Claw; 25, Gill I; 26, Gill IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208366/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), dorsal and ventral portions of lamellae of gills 2–7 wider and lanceolate, long and suddenly tapering at apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[152,1435,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 21. Foreleg; 22. Midleg; 23. Hindleg; 24, Claw; 25, Gill I; 26, Gill IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208366/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); (ii) Fore and mid femora with a regular row of long, thin setae on outer margin; denticles on claws progressively larger apically (
<figureCitation box="[494,634,838,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 26" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1988,2011]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[152,1435,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 26. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 21. Foreleg; 22. Midleg; 23. Hindleg; 24, Claw; 25, Gill I; 26, Gill IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208366/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Figs. 21–24</figureCitation>
); (iii) length of the labrum more than half of the width, lateral lobes rounded, anteriomedian emargination deeply cleft, apparently with 2 denticles; proximal transverse setal row laterally curved distally (
<figureCitation box="[438,578,910,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
); (iv) maxillary palp short, with long setae on third segment (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1378,910,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) and third segment of labial palp with 5–6 thick, spine-like setae on dorsal surface, inner and outer margins with short, thin setae (
<figureCitation box="[273,357,982,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,211,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 20. Larva of Klugephlebia kodai sp. n. 12. Dorsal view of male; 13. Dorsal view of female; 14. Ventral view of labrum; 15. Dorsal view of labrum; 16. Hypopharynx; 17. Left mandible; 18. Right mandible; 19. Maxillae; 20. Labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208365/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="383">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
